HEADWORD: Dogmatism
<hw>Dog"ma*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The manner or
character of a dogmatist; arrogance or positiveness in stating
opinion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The self-importance of his demeanor, and the <qex>dogmatism</qex>
of his conversation.</q> <rj><qau> Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dogmatist</ent>⟦br⟧
